<P> <P><b><i>
<font face="Georgia" size="4" color="#9F3215">
Milo Says:
</font></i></b><BR>

   What are these, trick questions?  Pass me that pipe.<P>

   I am not God.  I cannot bring a character model into existence merely
by uttering a magic word.  They take time to create, and when my bosses
want to put a few hundred different monsters in the game, well baby,
some geometry is going to get recycled.<P>

<HR align="center" width="85%"><P>

I have read a few of your answers Milo, and frankly I have to say that you must probably be one of the most cynical bastards around.<P>
 
 If you don't like people, then why don't you just quit "Ask Milo"?<P>

 Making jokes of people not being able to write decent English? Are you sure they even has English as their first language? What do you think a French would say about your language skills in his native language?<P>

 Making people feel like pricks because they write long letters, which they have invested a lot of time in?<P>

 Making fun about questions people think are serious enough to ask you?<P>
 
 I suggest that you don't answer the question if you don't like it. Don't make jokes on others, they might get hurt, and hurting people intentionally isn't very nice, is it?<P>

 And before you get sarcastic about my grammars, my first language isn't English.<P>

 Sverre Munthea<BR>
